[medium] policies/secretsmanager_vendor_credential_rotation.rego:84 (correctness)
Vendor rotation findings do not exclude service-linked secrets. With owning_service set, rotation_enabled=true, and no last_rotated_date, the policy still emits vendor_rotation_never_executed even though the bundle design and README say service-linked secrets are skipped from rotation checks because AWS owns those operations.
Suggested fix: Add not is_service_linked to vendor_rotation_never_executed and vendor_rotation_stale, and add a service-linked vendor-scoped test showing no rotation violation.
Guidance: Fix policies/secretsmanager_vendor_credential_rotation.rego. This is a customer-managed rotation policy, so service-linked secrets must be skipped under the design decision. Add a service-linked skip_reason for resource_type == "secret", is_vendor_secret, and is_service_linked, with wording matching rotation_configured such as Secret <arn> is service-linked (owning_service=<service>); rotation is AWS-managed. Add not is_service_linked to both violation bodies: vendor_rotation_never_executed and vendor_rotation_stale. Keep vendor tag scoping and allowed_unrotated_vendor_arns behavior unchanged. Add tests in policies/secretsmanager_vendor_credential_rotation_test.rego for a vendor-scoped service-linked secret with rotation_enabled=true and last_rotated_date == "" producing no vendor_rotation_never_executed, plus a stale service-linked secret producing no vendor_rotation_stale.
