[medium] policies/secretsmanager_privacy_subprocessor_posture.rego:151 (correctness)
The PI subprocessor posture policy skips service-linked secrets for rotation_disabled but not for rotation_overdue. A service-linked PI secret with AWS-owned rotation and an old last_rotated_date still gets a customer-managed rotation finding, which conflicts with the documented service-linked rotation skip behavior.
Suggested fix: Add not is_service_linked to the rotation_overdue violation while continuing to evaluate the non-rotation PI posture checks, and cover it with a service-linked PI test.
Guidance: Fix only the rotation_overdue check in policies/secretsmanager_privacy_subprocessor_posture.rego. Add not is_service_linked to the rotation_overdue violation, matching the existing rotation_disabled gate. Do not add a whole-policy service-linked skip_reason here, because this policy intentionally still evaluates KMS, tagging/vendor documentation, resource-policy principal, and action posture for service-linked PI secrets. Add a regression test in policies/secretsmanager_privacy_subprocessor_posture_test.rego with PrivacyScope set, owning_service non-empty, rotation_enabled=true, and an old last_rotated_date; assert rotation_overdue is absent while a non-rotation finding such as aws_managed_default_kms_key or principal_wildcard can still be evaluated when its inputs are present.
