[medium] policies/secretsmanager_confidential_rotation_required.rego:81 (correctness)
The confidential rotation policy skips service-linked secrets for rotation_disabled but still evaluates rotation_cadence_too_long. A service-linked confidential secret with AWS-managed rotation and automatically_after_days greater than the configured maximum is reported even though customer-managed rotation checks should skip service-linked secrets.
Suggested fix: Add not is_service_linked to rotation_cadence_too_long and add a test for a confidential service-linked secret with a long cadence that produces no rotation violation.
Guidance: Fix policies/secretsmanager_confidential_rotation_required.rego. Add not is_service_linked to the rotation_cadence_too_long violation, matching the existing rotation_disabled gate and the design that service-linked secrets are skipped for customer-managed rotation checks. Because this policy is entirely about rotation, it is acceptable to add a service-linked skip_reason for resource_type == "secret", is_confidential, and is_service_linked, with AWS-managed rotation wording. Do not change confidential classification detection or max_confidential_rotation_days. Add a test in policies/secretsmanager_confidential_rotation_required_test.rego for a confidential service-linked secret with rotation_enabled=true and automatically_after_days greater than data.max_confidential_rotation_days; assert no rotation_cadence_too_long violation and, if you add it, skip_reason is defined.
